title: DoorDash Sets IPO Terms Pushing Valuation as High as $32 Billion
sub_head: San Francisco food-delivery company to sell 33 million shares at $75 to $85 each
body:
DoorDash Inc. on Monday said it plans to sell 33 million shares in an initial public offering that could give the food-delivery company a valuation of as much as $32 billion.
The San Francisco company said it expects an offering price of between $75 and $85 a share, adding that a pricing at the $80 midpoint of that range would yield net proceeds of about $2.54 billion.
